== String usage example == A program that uses strings will at some point use Input and Output so to make things easy I'm going to write a simple program to explain it. public static void main(){ String myString = "Hello World"; // stores the string "Hello World" in the myString variable System.out.println(myString); // prints out myString to the screen System.out.println("like my program?"); // This will also print a string to the screen }
'''Exercise'''
Write a program with System.out.println(); and System.out.print(); and see if it makes any difference.

